\date{2024-09-06}
\title{colimit presentation of simplicial sets}
\taxon{proposition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}
\cite{riehl-2008-simplicial-sets}{Riehl}{p. 5}

\p{By the [density formula](rs-006B), a [simplicial set](rs-0080) #{X} is the
[colimit](rs-001Z) of each of its [standard simplices](rs-0084). As such, each
simplicial set is "glued together" from standard simplicies in a canonical way.}
